parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure to Honor Recall and Lack of Transparency
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to honor recalls and lack of transparency can lead to delayed or missed repairs, potentially causing accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Dealerships refusing to inspect or repair vehicles despite recall notices
manufacturers claiming recalls have been completed when they have not
lack of communication or transparency about recall status.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine component failures can cause engine fires, overheating, and damage to the vehicle, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: loud knocking or rattling noise from the engine block.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical wiring harness can cause a fire under the dash or in the engine compartment, leading to a loss of vehicle control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: Smoke or burning smell from under the dash or engine compartment

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the battery to drain, leading to a loss of vehicle control, accidents, or injuries.
The overheating of the exhaust manifold can cause a fire, leading to a loss of vehicle control, accidents, or injuries.
The failure of the emergency parking brake can cause the vehicle to roll or move unintentionally, potentially leading to accidents, injuries, or property damage.
symptoms: The emergency parking brake does not engage or disengage properly
the parking brake does not hold the vehicle in place
the parking brake fails to adjust or work properly
the parking brake only works intermittently.
